page.title: 13HAINAULT FOREST
page.content:
There are alot of pond birds, like the Mallard, Tufted Duck, Grebe, Moorhen, and the Coote.In the Summer, Swallows and Martins sweep over the water, taking food on the wing. In the woods, the Finch and Jay can be seen flying for cover.
In Hainault Forest, you may be able to see the Yellow Lesser Celendine. Among the bluish flowers, are the Dog Violet, Forget Me Not, Ground Ivy, and Bugle. The Forest also has grassland, hedges, shrubs, and plantations, where the following can be seen: Ox-Eye Daisy Speedwell, Foxglove, Tormentil, Rose bay Willow Herb, Woody Nightshade, and White Bryony. The red berries from the White Bryony are POISONOUS.}
